<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>emsenn.net</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/</link><description>Recent content on emsenn.net</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title/><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-codomain/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-codomain/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="relational-codomain"&gt;Relational Codomain&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-is"&gt;What this is&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;codomain&lt;/strong&gt; of a morphism in &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;R&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;R&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the object the morphism arrives at — its output end.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the relational universe, the central morphisms are induced by the contravariant fiber doctrine &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;o&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;p&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;u&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;l&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H : T^{\mathrm{op}} \to \mathbf{HA_{nucl}}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;a href="functor.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Functor&lt;/a&gt;).
For a prefix morphism &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;f : t \to t&amp;#x27;&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in the history category &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the induced map is &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H(f) : H_{t&amp;#x27;} \to H_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.
The codomain of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H(f)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — the fiber at &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the &lt;strong&gt;source&lt;/strong&gt; of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;f&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-domain/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-domain/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="relational-domain"&gt;Relational Domain&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-is"&gt;What this is&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;domain&lt;/strong&gt; of a morphism in &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;R&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;R&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the object the morphism departs from — its input end.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the relational universe, the central morphisms are induced by the contravariant fiber doctrine &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;o&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;p&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;u&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;l&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H : T^{\mathrm{op}} \to \mathbf{HA_{nucl}}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;a href="functor.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Functor&lt;/a&gt;).
For a prefix morphism &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;f : t \to t&amp;#x27;&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in the history category &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the induced map is &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H(f) : H_{t&amp;#x27;} \to H_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.
The domain of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H(f)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H_{t&amp;#x27;}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — the fiber at &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;t&amp;#x27;&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the &lt;strong&gt;target&lt;/strong&gt; of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;f&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-entity/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-entity/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="relational-entity"&gt;Relational Entity&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-is"&gt;What this is&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;RelationalEntity&lt;/strong&gt; is an &lt;a href="entity.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Entity&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href="relations-system.md" class="link-internal"&gt;R&lt;/a&gt; — an element of the relational universe.
It is in R by &lt;a href="../math/closure-operator.md" class="link-internal"&gt;U_G&lt;/a&gt; condition 1: X ⊆ U_G(X).
Whatever is fed in is already in the closure.
There are no invalid entities, only entities at different depths in the &lt;a href="../math/depth-filtration.md" class="link-internal"&gt;depth filtration&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A RelationalEntity is not defined by what category it belongs to.
It is defined by which relations it carries.
Each relation present is a relation it stands in; the union of those relations is what the entity IS.
A RelationalEntity MUST carry &lt;a href="id.md" class="link-internal"&gt;id&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="description.md" class="link-internal"&gt;description&lt;/a&gt; to satisfy condition 2.
Every relation key it carries MUST itself be a specced entity — see &lt;a href="relational-system-markdown.md" class="link-internal"&gt;relational-system-markdown&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-operation/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-operation/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="relational-operation"&gt;Relational Operation&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-is"&gt;What this is&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;RelationalOperation&lt;/strong&gt; is an &lt;a href="operation.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Operation&lt;/a&gt; whose carrier is (a part of) the relational universe R = Sh(T, J).
It maps R, or a fiber of R, or a class of objects of R, within itself.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The canonical instances are the three acts and the two nuclei:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Operation&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Carrier&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Arity&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Source&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Nucleus σ_t&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Fiber H_t&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;1&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="../math/relational-history-saturation-nucleus.md" class="link-internal"&gt;relational-history-saturation-nucleus&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Nucleus Δ_t&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Fiber H_t&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;1&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="../math/relational-history-transfer-nucleus.md" class="link-internal"&gt;relational-history-transfer-nucleus&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Sequential act G_s&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;R&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;1&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="../math/sequential-act.md" class="link-internal"&gt;sequential-act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Concurrent act ⊛&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;R × R&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;2&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="../math/concurrent-act.md" class="link-internal"&gt;concurrent-act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Generative act U_G&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;P(Obj(R))&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;1&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="../math/generative-act.md" class="link-internal"&gt;generative-act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each of these maps a carrier within itself.
None of them are morphisms between different objects — they are all endofunctions on their respective carriers.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-source/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-source/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="relational-source"&gt;Relational Source&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-is"&gt;What this is&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;source&lt;/strong&gt; of a morphism &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;f : t \to t&amp;#x27;&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in the history category &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — the shorter history from which the prefix map departs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Source is a concept at the level of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the history category.
It is not a concept at the level of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;R&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;R&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the relational universe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This distinction matters because the fiber doctrine &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;o&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;p&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;u&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;l&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H : T^{\mathrm{op}} \to \mathbf{HA_{nucl}}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is contravariant (&lt;a href="functor.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Functor&lt;/a&gt;).
For &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;f : t \to t&amp;#x27;&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the induced map is &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H(f) : H_{t&amp;#x27;} \to H_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — direction reversed.
The source of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;f&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, but the codomain of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H(f)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;R&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;R&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; also lands at &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.
Source and codomain share a location, but they are not the same concept.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-state/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-state/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="relational-state"&gt;Relational State&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-is"&gt;What this is&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;RelationalState&lt;/strong&gt; is the &lt;a href="state.md" class="link-internal"&gt;State&lt;/a&gt; type of a &lt;a href="relational-machine.md" class="link-internal"&gt;RelationalMachine&lt;/a&gt;.
It is a presheaf &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;M&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;Σ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator="true"&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;I&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;o&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;p&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;u&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;l&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H: M(\Sigma, I)^{op} \to \mathbf{HA}_\mathrm{nucl}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;: a family of fiber Heyting algebras &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; indexed by histories &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∈&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;M&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;Σ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator="true"&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;I&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;t \in M(\Sigma, I)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, with restriction maps &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;ρ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\rho: H_{t&amp;#x27;} \to H_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; for &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;≤&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;t \leq t&amp;#x27;&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A RelationalState is not a single fiber.
It is the entire indexed family — all fibers simultaneously present, connected by the restriction maps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="sections-and-fibers"&gt;Sections and fibers&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;section&lt;/strong&gt; of the RelationalState at history &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — the fiber Heyting algebra at that history.
&lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is what the RelationalMachine holds &amp;ldquo;in focus&amp;rdquo; at history &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — formally, a &lt;a href="focus.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Focus&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator="true"&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;(H, t)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-target/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-target/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="relational-target"&gt;Relational Target&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-is"&gt;What this is&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;target&lt;/strong&gt; of a morphism &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;f : t \to t&amp;#x27;&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in the history category &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;t&amp;#x27;&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — the longer history at which the prefix map arrives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Target is a concept at the level of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the history category.
It is not a concept at the level of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;R&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;R&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the relational universe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This distinction matters because the fiber doctrine &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;o&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;p&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;u&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;l&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H : T^{\mathrm{op}} \to \mathbf{HA_{nucl}}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is contravariant (&lt;a href="functor.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Functor&lt;/a&gt;).
For &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;f : t \to t&amp;#x27;&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the induced map is &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H(f) : H_{t&amp;#x27;} \to H_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — direction reversed.
The target of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;f&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;t&amp;#x27;&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, but the domain of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H(f)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;R&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;R&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; departs from &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;H_{t&amp;#x27;}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.
Target and domain share a location, but they are not the same concept.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-unit/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-unit/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="relational-unit"&gt;Relational Unit&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Superseded.&lt;/strong&gt; This concept has been renamed to &lt;a href="relational-entity.md" class="link-internal"&gt;RelationalEntity&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Three-domain research found that &amp;ldquo;Entity&amp;rdquo; is more precisely correct than &amp;ldquo;Unit&amp;rdquo;:
it is the canonical name in BWW/FRISCO ontology and knowledge-graph formalisms for a named, addressable individual that can carry properties.
&amp;ldquo;Unit&amp;rdquo; is a false cognate: in type theory it names the terminal type (the one-element type); in algebra it names the multiplicative identity.
Both meanings cause confusion for formally trained readers.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Relating</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relating/</link><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relating/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="relating"&gt;Relating&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A conversation is not a thing that exists and then, separately, involves people talking. A conversation &lt;em&gt;is&lt;/em&gt; the talking. If the turns stop being taken and understood, the conversation doesn&amp;rsquo;t pause — it ends. Relating is this kind of activity: the ongoing work that holds things together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href="./relational-dynamics.md" class="link-internal"&gt;relational dynamics&lt;/a&gt;, relating is the core process. It is not a state but an activity — something that must keep happening for the thing it sustains to persist. The stone on the desk exists through the ongoing relating of gravity, friction, and surface. The school club exists through the ongoing relating of meetings called, rooms opened, members showing up. When the relating stops, the thing it held together comes apart.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Relational dynamics</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-dynamics/</link><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/relational-dynamics/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="relational-dynamics"&gt;Relational dynamics&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A conversation persists only because turns keep being taken and understood. A school club persists only because meetings are called, rooms are opened, members show up. A stone on a desk persists only because gravity, friction, and a surface hold it there. In each case, what exists, exists through ongoing relational activity. Relational dynamics is the framework that takes this observation seriously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Relational dynamics is a way of paying attention that treats everything as held together by relations. Rather than asking &amp;ldquo;what is this thing?&amp;rdquo; it asks &amp;ldquo;what has to be happening for this to keep going?&amp;rdquo; This shift — from substance to process, from entity to activity — is the framework&amp;rsquo;s core move. It is grounded in Lakota epistemologies and developed by emsenn.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>The Five Mathematical Systems</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/five-mathematical-systems/</link><pubDate>Wed, 04 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/five-mathematical-systems/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Relationality is formalized through four mathematical universes, organized by two independent axes: internal character (process versus structure) and validation target (mathematical correspondence versus empirical correspondence). Together with relationality itself — the incited derivation that concerns the same domain as all four — these constitute five mathematical systems.&lt;/p&gt;
