&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Plus:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="../index.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Relationality&lt;/a&gt; — the philosophical-mathematical framework that concerns the same domain as all four universes.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/writing_standard/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/terms/writing_standard/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="how-to-make-text-good"&gt;How to make text good&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a procedure.
Follow the steps in order on any text you write or edit.
The standard is plain American English as defined by the Federal Plain Language Guidelines (plainlanguage.gov), adapted for mathematical and technical content.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The goal is clarity, specificity, and plainness.
Not elegance.
Not style.
The reader must understand every sentence on the first reading.
The Plain Writing Act of 2010 defines the standard: &amp;ldquo;writing that is clear, concise, well-organized, and follows other best practices appropriate to the subject or field and intended audience.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>